      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The first step in the metabolism of glycerol, formed by digestion of fats, is phosphorylation of the pro-<i>R</i> – CH<sub>2</sub>OH group by reaction with adenosine triphosphate (ATP) to give the corresponding glycerol phosphate plus adenosine diphosphate (ADP). Show the stereochemistry of the product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbzRSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--26158a664ffbfdc34ea413d5b3bb5d885e6b81d2/OChem_05_EC_024.jpg\" alt=\"The figure shows a reaction where glycerol on the conversion of A T P to A D P forms glycerol phosphate.\">",
